cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper deals with indoor wireless communication and proposes a statistical path loss model for the 2.4 - 2.5 GHz ISM band. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The proposed model can be used for the deployment and operations of IoT and cloud robotics, indicating a potential fit for cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
